cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.RO

This paper presents a novel algorithm for optimization using a cooperative group of agents, specifically ants. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) which deals with optimization and learning algorithms inspired by natural systems. The paper also discusses the use of individual and social learning, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of a group of agents also falls under the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the optimization problem used in the experiments is the traveling salesman problem, which falls under the sub-category of cs.RO (Robotics).
